                            <comment id="14554948" author="JIRAUSER19808" created="Fri, 27 Jan 2023 01:45:02 -0800"  >[~sswsharm], [~thartmann], [~fyang] Hi, I have created a pull request to provide more detailed information that current RISC-V port only supports up to sv48: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/pull/12247&quot;&gt;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/pull/12247&lt;/a&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14554329" author="fyang" created="Wed, 25 Jan 2023 04:01:05 -0800"  >[~thartmann] Yes, you are right.&lt;br/&gt;
[~fjiang] Could you please add some extra information so that the error msg reported is easier for the users to understand? Thanks.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
There isn&amp;#39;t a plan to support sv57 in the short term. As a workaround, QEMU users may use some older kernel versions. If they need higher kernel versions, they need to do a small change on QEMU to force QEMU to use sv48 in place of sv57 and rebuild QEMU. Previously discussed is here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://mail.openjdk.org/pipermail/riscv-port-dev/2022-October/000647.html&quot;&gt;https://mail.openjdk.org/pipermail/riscv-port-dev/2022-October/000647.html&lt;/a&gt;</comment>
